FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions
================================

Q: What is 'pidgin-osd'?
A: 'pidgin-osd' is an application to print pidgin events to the X
   console.

Q: What is needed?
A: You need a working pidgin.

Q: Are there any differences between 'pidgin-osd' and 'gaimnosd'?
A: Yes. The glib and pidgin returns any incoming message as UTF-8
   to the plugins, but if you don't use UTF-8 you will not see the
   special characters. This was fixed in 'pidgin-osd'.
